ref: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.19, p.380 (1974)
title: Relative yields of delayed neutrons in fission of Np-237 by 0.4-1.2 MeV neutrons

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.19, p.380 (1974)

x4freetext: Eng.transl.of YF,19,(4),748,1974

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Yadernaya Fizika, Vol.19, Issue.4, p.748 (1974)

x4freetext: Data and graphs are given
Relative yields of delayed neutrons in fission of
Np-237 by 0.4-1.2 MeV neutrons
No information
No information
Proton-tritium . 1-mg/cm2 target.
Width of neutron spectrum ~ 200 to 100 keV .
The decay curves were recorded with channel width of
1 sec for a period of 1024 sec after 5min bombardment
of sample. Cooling time 6 sec.
HLs data of G.R.Keepin ( Physics of Nucl.Kinetics,
Addison-Wesley,1964; Rus.transl.- Atomizdat,1967,p.100)
for Pu-239 were used for yields calculation by least
squares method.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Error was calculated from the inverse matrix
for individual series; average of several series of
measurement.
Compiled at the centre CJD
date and reaction field were corrected
SD: Ref. on Engl.transl. of YF added.
M.M. Article was checked, BIB information
was corrected in TITLE, AUTHOR,
REL was deleted, REACTION was coded as ratio;
ARB-UNITS -> NO-DIM .
